caption: We frequent Kai Sushi in South Loop almost once per week, and it’s one of our favorite joints in the entire city. Staff is super friendly, the food is delicious, and prices very reasonable! BYOB is nice

The staff is quick and friendly to make everything as good as possible. Overall, the experience was great and I will definitely look at coming back again. If you're in the Chinatown area, stop by and grab a bite to eat, this place is a must.

Great sushi spot in the south loop! I have ordered from here many times in the past And didn’t know it was BYOB until today which was a nice surprise! Friendly staff, nice atmosphere, and the quality of the fresh fish was amazing! Will definitely be back :)
Deliciousness ane great service every. Time.
Good and fresh sushi. We were the only ones eating in restaurant
I go here all the time this is my spot for sushis, just wish there was a loyalty program lol.
This is a pretty good hole in the wall sushi restaurant. Prices were fair and good quality roll. Only thing that stunk was they had no sake. BYOB. I would totally dine here again.

Another delicious dinner from Kai Sushi tonight. Ingredients are fresh and tasty, our orders are always ready on time, and staff are efficient and courteous. Ordered online through their website (they use ChowNow), which was easy to use, and was able to place the order in advance and select my preferred pick-up time. They are not currently doing any in person dining, but their takeout game is on point! On several larger orders we have placed, they have also thrown in a free appetizer, which is excellent customer service--and great marketing, as we now order shumai every time because a freebie became one of my son's favorites!
It’s nice to have places like this nearby. Always fresh and delicious! Very easy to make an order for a pick up over the phone.
One of my favorite places near my home.  Fish is fresh and ordering takeout through ChowNow is so convenient.

10/10 would recommend. For a better experience use soy sauce. Can’t go wrong with anything honestly just know what foods you don’t like.

it was ok :// we came in late & the staff was low key mean but it’s ok

Finding parking near this restaurant is a real challenge so make sure you try to beat the lunch time rush. I got the mild sandwich combo and it was juicy and tender. Mild wasn't too hot and the atmosphere was pretty chill. The meal was definitely enough to keep me full for the rest of the day.

Disclaimer- I got Kai Sushi via delivery.  First of all, the ingredients all had a low quality fishy stench- as though they had been sitting out for a long time even though the delivery time was very fast. Even the seaweed salad did not taste fresh. Second, neither of the specialty rolls were very well crafted. They fell apart, and the recipes were strange- it all sounded good on the menu but the execution was really weird. Finally, both my boyfriend and I had stomach cramps after eating this. Can’t be sure it’s related, can’t be sure that it’s not. Won’t be ordering from here again- there’s too much other good sushi in Chicago.

Kai sushi called me themselves that they mixed up the order and offered to make a new order for us free of charge. That is great customer service!  Shout out to the management for taking care of your customers during this pandemic. Support your local business and enjoy sushi !

3.5 stars. I kid you not when I say I've passed this place hundreds of times. Three years later, I finally made a stop. Two of us shared the sushi platter (15 pieces), Chicago fire roll, and lobster mania roll. The tuna that came with the sushi platter was no good. It was room temperature/warmish. The other fish on the platter was pretty decent. I really liked the Chicago fire roll. The fish was chilled and there was a decent amount in it. The lobster mania roll was good too, a tad too spicy for me, but enjoyable.  The fish overall wasn't horrible, but not the greatest. It was fresh enough for me not to throw up after, but it also didn't melt in my mouth. Reason for my return would be because of convenience rather than for quality. Our waitress was so patient and kind. When we first walked in we were deciding between outside and inside. We sat outside, she brought us waters and was handing us menus as we decided that we wanted to sit inside again because it was too windy. She was attentive and made sure to check up on us every here and there - making sure we had what we needed but not making us feel like she was rushing us.

I have just had the most humiliating experience of my LIFE!!! We recently visited Kai for a late Sunday lunch. After ordering WAY TOO MUCH FOOD, and the waiter John (the blonde guy) didn't even advise that we were ordering way too much. He totally took advantage of us and doubled up on a bunch of items because it was four of us instead of telling us that the plate only came with 2 pieces. We finally took a bunch a food to go to give it to a homeless and paid for our food (TIP WAS INCLUDED for 4 people, which I've actually never heard of). After signing our bill and walking out and waiting for our uber, this server has marched out and has yelled "was there something wrong with your service? Why was there not a tip included in your payment?" Omg!!!! I can not believe this just happened in front of all the customers sitting outside of the restaurant! We immediately told him to recheck the bill that the tip was included in the total. He simply came out after checking and said, "yes, you are right " and closed the front door in our face. I can not believe this just happened. Even if we had not left a tip, this should never happened as tip is totally optional in any establishment. We actually left the tip that the bill included. I will NEVER recommend this restaurant to anyone.

Love it....
Very fresh. Reasonably priced.

Sushi here is really good: fresh and good quality fish in nice portions and affordable prices. My favorite was the sunset roll with salmon and lemon, it was a great combination! Don't be fooled by the name Chicago fire, it's not spicy, but a tasty roll nevertheless. The tuna roll, salmon and avocado roll and Alaskan roll are all delicious. The squid salad with Asian vegetables was only disappointing because it came with lettuce and carrots...I was expecting something more exotic. The seaweed salad is light, fresh and flavorful.  The room is clean and staff friendly. However, they ration the water, I got one glass of water that was removed when empty long before the meal was over. I had a ginger ale as well but hydration with water seems like a basic necessity to me. We had edamame but staff kept taking the little dishes away leaving us to put the shells on the table. A bit strange but all can be ignored because the sushi is really good.

This place rocks! The sushi is delicious! I ordered the Chicago Fire roll and the Cruncy roll. I give it a 5/5. It is a very laid back, chill environment. Not fancy, a good place to go when you want to chill with some friends. The sushi is moderately priced. It is also BYOB.

This BYOB sushi spot is very good and reasonably priced. We recently hosted a get together and they accommodated a very large take out order. Everyone enjoyed their rolls and the portions were generous.

Stopped here for dinner last week. Very unpretentious place, not elegant. Paper napkins, folded paper menus. Don't go here for the atmosphere. That said, service with a smile and excellent sushi at a good price. If you're looking for a quiet place for some excellent sushi, this is it.

We saw the BYOB sign outside of Kai one night and decided to check it out. My husband called to see how much the corkage fee was - none! So we grabbed a bottle of wine from home and went on a Friday evening around 8:30. The place wasn't full, there's probably around 10-12 tables inside and outdoor seating. Decor is very minimalistic and you mark off your order on paper menus - this is definitely not a fancy sushi place.  We were given some cucumber salad to munch on while we looked through the menu. About 10 or so minutes after placing our order, our waiter brought us complimentary edamame to apologize for how long we were waiting. We ordered 2 rolls and salmon sushi, which was plenty of food for us. The bonito flakes were a nice touch on the Flaming VIP roll, and the salmon sushi was fresh. We were easily convinced into ordering dessert - tempura fried banana with green tea ice cream. The portion is huge, and it only costs $6. Win.  Since our first few visits, Kai has gotten increasingly popular and unfortunately their service has gone a bit downhill. One Saturday evening I came in with a friend and were asked if we had a reservation (apparently they take them now). We didn't, but they sat us anyway. They did, however, seem to rush us through our mail. When we were close to finishing our rolls, our waitress kept asking if we were done and if we could pay the check. Another time when we sat outside, our waiter was incredibly slow - didn't refill our waters, food took awhile to come out, etc.  Everything is really reasonably priced, given the size of the rolls and quality of the fish. If you're looking for a fancy sushi place, go elsewhere. Otherwise, Kai is a great casual place for good sushi.

The sushi was great and love the prices especially since other places in the South Loop have overpriced sushi but not this one. It has a very warm and friendly environment and you see families, friends reuniting, and dates all around. My mom and I got the West Town Sushi (which I liked but my mother didn't) and the Chicago Fire (which was vice versa). The Sweet Potato fry sushi or whatever its called was so good we ordered seconds. Its also BYOB. The staff is super nice, I totally think its worth checking out (and my mom loved the price compared to other sushi places).
Absolutely a great place for sushi.  Service is excellent and caring.  Very friendly staff and delicious food from the rolls to appetizers make this a must stop if you are looking for sushi.

Great South Loop sushi option with a friendly staff and tasty rolls. The blossom, ocean, volcano rolls were all excellent picks with ocean being my favorite. The chef also gave us a taste of the salmon collar salad which was a first for me. We will definitely become repeat customers. They also do takeout.
Contempary sushi! Pls open a place in San Francisco. Great service, fresh and DELICIOUS sushi. Thanks Kai team!
Love the neighborhood sushi joint ! Really cozy space where you can get to know the chef guy. Awesome specials and super fresh food. Pretty sure it's all from Lake Michigan
Great sushi in the south loop! BYOB makes the experience great and the rolls are all delish! We're excited to have such good sushi in the neighborhood
Great sushi at reasonable prices. They allow dogs on the patio which is a plus. Chicago Fire and Volcano rolls are a must.
